REFERENCES,0.4847775175644028,"Here, the cj’s and rj’s correspond to the column sums and row sums of the iterating matrix in the
above informal description. Let diag(x) be a diagonal matrix whose diagonal is x. The following
result is proved by Sinkhorn & Knopp (1967)."
REFERENCES,0.48711943793911006,Under review as a conference paper at ICLR 2022
REFERENCES,0.4894613583138173,"Theorem 4 (Sinkhorn–Knopp). If K0 is nonnegative, then a necessary and sufﬁcient condition that
the iteration (15) converges is that K0 has total support. Let positive vectors c∗and r∗be the limits
of {cj} and {rj}, respectively. The matrix diag(r∗)K0 diag(c∗) is doubly stochastic."
REFERENCES,0.4918032786885246,"This result, however, does not give the convergence speed. In order to obtain a tight one, we fol-
low Knight (2008) and perform a minor modiﬁcation of (15):"
